HEADWORD: Spirograph
<hw>Spi"ro*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spirare</ets> to breathe + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for recording the respiratory
movements, as the sphygmograph does those of the pulse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spirometer</ent>⟦br⟧
